info.headline: Wind Advisory issued December 13 at 6:05PM PST until December 15 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Eureka
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM TO 4 PM PST WEDNESDAY... * WHAT...South winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 50 mph expected. * WHERE...Del Norte Interior, Northern Humboldt Coast, Southwestern Humboldt, Northern Humboldt Interior, Southern Humboldt Interior, Northwestern Mendocino Interior, Northeastern Mendocino Interior and Southeastern Mendocino Interior Counties. * WHEN...From 10 AM to 4 PM PST Wednesday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
